                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/231: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-24T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 24, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 27—11:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>114. The Chinese Director of Telegraphs wishes to know when Federal Company’s
                    representatives will probably reach China as in accordance with Washington
                    Conference agreement he is arranging to take over foreign wireless plants in
                    China. He desires telegraphic reply. The Director believes it is possible to use
                    some of this equipment in construction by the Federal Telegraph Company and with
                    others out of the fight thinks the prospects are especially favorable for the
                    Federal Company. It is considered important by the Legation that the despatch of
                    its agents to China to start construction and other work should be hastened by
                    the Federal Telegraph Company.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
